column3: Osment at Crescent Cove is vexed by litter in the area.
A merchant from Limsa Lominsa has left rubbish scattered about the docks. Clean it up as a service to the distressed Osment.
You have finished cleaning up the rubbish that littered the docks. Speak to Osment once more.
Though cleanliness has been restored, Osment is already lamenting the next Lominsan sloth who will darken his docks.
Clean up the rubbish on the docks.
Ugggh, what a pain in the bloody arse. Who do those Lominsans think they are, anyway?
Just look at all this, would you? A merchant from Limsa Lominsa dumped this junk when he shipped out. Claimed it wasn't fit for sellin', so he just up and left it!
Barbarians! What passes for etiquette across the Strait of Merlthor?
Don't suppose I could ask you to clean up the rest for me, eh? Please? I've picked up so much junk already, the mere sight of it fair makes me gag.
Thank you, friend. Seeing this place clean again does my spirit good.
Though, I suppose some other Lominsan merchant will be by before long and leave more filth behind. <sigh> I hate my life.
